ISLAMABAD, Dec 27 (APP): Caretaker Federal Minister for Information, Broadcasting and Parliamentary Affairs Murtaza Solangi on Wednesday said 16th martyrdom anniversary of former prime minister Benazir Bhutto was a stark reminder that violent extremism, in its all manifestations, shades, colours, shrouds and ideologies, remained an existential threat for Pakistan.
Using his X account, he said the war against terrorism and extremism, was the long one, “but we shall win it, Insha Allah.”
